---
import DocsLayout from '../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<DocsLayout title="Brute Force Protection" activeNav="brute-force-protection" description="Account lockout with 6 password rules and HIBP breach detection.">

  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Araxys protects authentication endpoints from brute force attacks through a three-layer approach: <strong>account
    lockout</strong> after repeated failures (returns <code>423 Locked</code>), a <strong>6-rule password policy</strong>
    that enforces complexity requirements, and optional <strong>Have I Been Pwned</strong> (HIBP) integration that checks
    passwords against known breach databases using the k-anonymity API.
  </p>

  <h2 id="how-it-works">How It Works</h2>

  <h3 id="account-lockout">Account Lockout</h3>
  <p>
    After <code>max_attempts</code> consecutive failed login attempts, Araxys locks the account and returns
    <code>423 Locked</code> for all subsequent attempts. The lockout lasts for <code>lockout_duration</code> seconds
    before the counter resets automatically. Successful logins reset the failure counter.
  </p>

  <h3 id="password-rules">Password Policy Rules</h3>
  <p>Araxys enforces six configurable password rules:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong><code>min_length</code></strong> — Minimum password length (default: 8)</li>
    <li><strong><code>require_upper</code></strong> — At least one uppercase letter required (default: <code>True</code>)</li>
    <li><strong><code>require_lower</code></strong> — At least one lowercase letter required (default: <code>True</code>)</li>
    <li><strong><code>require_digit</code></strong> — At least one digit required (default: <code>True</code>)</li>
    <li><strong><code>require_special</code></strong> — At least one special character required (default: <code>False</code>)</li>
    <li><strong><code>reject_common</code></strong> — Reject passwords from a built-in common password list (default: <code>True</code>)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 id="hibp">Have I Been Pwned Integration</h3>
  <p>
    When <code>hibp_enabled=True</code>, Araxys sends the <strong>first 5 characters of the SHA-1 hash</strong> of the
    password to the <a href="https://haveibeenpwned.com/API/v3" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HIBP k-anonymity API</a>
    (v5). The API returns all matching hash suffixes, and Araxys checks if the full hash appears in the response.
    If a match is found, the password is rejected with a <em>"Password has been compromised"</em> error.
  </p>
  <p>
    The integration uses the <strong>k-anonymity API</strong> — only the first 5 characters of the SHA-1 hash are sent over the network. With <code>hibp_fail_closed=True</code> (v0.10 default), Araxys properly rejects passwords when the HIBP API is unreachable rather than silently allowing them. This prevents attackers from DDoSing the HIBP API to bypass breach detection.
  </p>

  <h2 id="configuration">Configuration</h2>
  <p>Configure brute force protection via the <code>BruteForceConfig</code> model:</p>

  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">python</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code><span class="token-keyword">from</span> araxys <span class="token-keyword">import</span> AraxysConfig, AraxysShield
<span class="token-keyword">from</span> araxys.core.config <span class="token-keyword">import</span> BruteForceConfig

shield = <span class="token-function">AraxysShield</span>(
    app,
    <span class="token-function">AraxysConfig</span>(
        <span class="token-param">secret_key</span>=<span class="token-string">"your-32-char-secret-key-here!!!!"</span>,
        <span class="token-param">brute_force</span>=<span class="token-function">BruteForceConfig</span>(
            <span class="token-param">max_attempts</span>=<span class="token-number">5</span>,
            <span class="token-param">lockout_duration</span>=<span class="token-number">900</span>,
            <span class="token-param">password_rules</span>=&#123;
                <span class="token-string">"min_length"</span>: <span class="token-number">12</span>,
                <span class="token-string">"require_upper"</span>: <span class="token-bool">True</span>,
                <span class="token-string">"require_lower"</span>: <span class="token-bool">True</span>,
                <span class="token-string">"require_digit"</span>: <span class="token-bool">True</span>,
                <span class="token-string">"require_special"</span>: <span class="token-bool">True</span>,
                <span class="token-string">"reject_common"</span>: <span class="token-bool">True</span>,
            &#125;,
            <span class="token-param">hibp_enabled</span>=<span class="token-bool">True</span>,
        ),
    ),
)</code></pre>
  </div>

  <h3 id="config-reference">Configuration Reference</h3>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Field</th>
        <th>Type</th>
        <th>Default</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>max_attempts</code></td><td><code>int</code></td><td><code>5</code></td><td>Failed attempts before lockout</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>lockout_duration</code></td><td><code>int</code></td><td><code>900</code></td><td>Lockout duration in seconds</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>password_rules</code></td><td><code>dict</code></td><td><code>&#123;"min_length": 8, "require_upper": True, "require_lower": True, "require_digit": True, "require_special": False, "reject_common": True&#125;</code></td><td>Password policy</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>hibp_enabled</code></td><td><code>bool</code></td><td><code>True</code></td><td>Enable HIBP check</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <div class="alert alert--warning">
    <div class="alert-title">
      <span class="material-symbols-outlined" style="font-size: 16px;">warning</span>
      HIBP Fail-Closed (v0.10)
    </div>
    <div class="alert-content">
      When <code>hibp_fail_closed=True</code> (the default since v0.10), password validation <strong>raises an exception</strong> if the HIBP API is unreachable. This is a security hardening measure — it prevents attackers from DDoSing the HIBP API to bypass breach detection. If you need the old best-effort behavior, set <code>hibp_fail_closed=False</code>.
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="code-examples">Code Examples</h2>

  <h3>Custom Rules Per User Role</h3>
  <p>You can define different password rules for different user roles by creating multiple configs:</p>

  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">python</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code><span class="token-comment"># Strict rules for admin accounts</span>
admin_rules = <span class="token-function">BruteForceConfig</span>(
    <span class="token-param">max_attempts</span>=<span class="token-number">3</span>,
    <span class="token-param">lockout_duration</span>=<span class="token-number">1800</span>,
    <span class="token-param">password_rules</span>=&#123;
        <span class="token-string">"min_length"</span>: <span class="token-number">16</span>,
        <span class="token-string">"require_upper"</span>: <span class="token-bool">True</span>,
        <span class="token-string">"require_lower"</span>: <span class="token-bool">True</span>,
        <span class="token-string">"require_digit"</span>: <span class="token-bool">True</span>,
        <span class="token-string">"require_special"</span>: <span class="token-bool">True</span>,
        <span class="token-string">"reject_common"</span>: <span class="token-bool">True</span>,
    &#125;,
    <span class="token-param">hibp_enabled</span>=<span class="token-bool">True</span>,
)

<span class="token-comment"># Relaxed rules for read-only API tokens</span>
api_rules = <span class="token-function">BruteForceConfig</span>(
    <span class="token-param">max_attempts</span>=<span class="token-number">10</span>,
    <span class="token-param">lockout_duration</span>=<span class="token-number">300</span>,
    <span class="token-param">password_rules</span>=&#123;
        <span class="token-string">"min_length"</span>: <span class="token-number">8</span>,
        <span class="token-string">"require_upper"</span>: <span class="token-bool">False</span>,
        <span class="token-string">"require_lower"</span>: <span class="token-bool">False</span>,
        <span class="token-string">"require_digit"</span>: <span class="token-bool">False</span>,
        <span class="token-string">"require_special"</span>: <span class="token-bool">False</span>,
        <span class="token-string">"reject_common"</span>: <span class="token-bool">False</span>,
    &#125;,
    <span class="token-param">hibp_enabled</span>=<span class="token-bool">False</span>,
)</code></pre>
  </div>

  <h2 id="integration">Integration</h2>
  <p>
    The brute force module integrates with the <strong>Audit Logging</strong> system — each failed login attempt is
    logged with the client IP, username, and current attempt count. Successful logins after a lockout period also
    emit an audit event.
  </p>
  <p>
    In the middleware chain, brute force protection sits <strong>after</strong> rate limiting but <strong>before</strong>
    the request handler. This ensures that rate limiting catches volumetric attacks first, while brute force protection
    handles targeted credential stuffing against specific accounts.
  </p>

</DocsLayout>
